          Instead of “I can’t do this,” think: “I can’t do this yet.” 
          Track small wins, visualize success, and challenge limiting beliefs. Journaling rewires cognitive bias. Confidence isn’t a gift—it’s built like muscle. 
          Your mind glows before your life does.
