      <p class="blog-title">2. How I Elevated My Aesthetic on a Budget ✨</p>
      <div class="blog-content">
        <p>
          I didn’t suddenly become a Pinterest girl. I started with what I had. I chose 2 colors I loved and began curating clothes, notebooks, and decor around that theme. 
          I deep-cleaned my room, added fairy lights, and started dressing like the version of me I admired. 
          It’s not about money—it’s about alignment. Romanticizing everyday routines made me feel expensive, even in a thrifted outfit.
        </p>
      </div>
