    <div class="blog-card" onclick="toggleBlog(this)">
      <p class="blog-title">3. Mentally Healing When No One Notices 🧠</p>
      <div class="blog-content">
        <p>
          Healing isn’t always aesthetic. It’s crying in silence, forgiving without apologies, and choosing peace even when you want closure. 
          I began with 5-minute meditations, limiting social media, and writing one thing I was proud of daily. 
          I didn’t magically become healed—but I became self-aware. That was enough to start again, softly and steadily.
        </p>
      </div>
